<TITLE> Dhaka-Ctg rail connection severed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  Rail communication between Dhaka and Chittagong was severed from early Monday when a freight train went off the tracks in Feni. Rescue of the derailed train is underway. Several trains were stranded at railway stations along the route until 10.30am. Matiur Rahman, senior deputy assistant engineer of Bangladesh Railway (east zone), told reporters that two carriages of the Dhaka-bound freight train derailed near Feni's Fazilpur station at around 3.00am. There were no casualties. He said the rail link would be restored soon. bd
